column12: METHODS AND COMPOSITIONS FOR TREATING ATHEROSCLEROSIS
column13: The current disclosure provides methods and compositions for treating atherosclerosis, and is based on inhibiting anti-angiogenesis in vivo. Aspects relate to a method for treating atherosclerosis in a subject comprising: administering a surgical treatment to a subject determined to have one or more of: increased levels of HGF, decreased levels of VEGF165a, increased levels of VEGFR1, increased levels of endostatin, and/or increased levels of angiostatin.

column12: COMPONENT CART ASSEMBLY
column13: A cart assembly includes a base with wheels, a shelf support structure orthogonally arranged with respect to the base, one or more shelves supported by the support structure, and a swivel mechanism. The swivel mechanism is coupled to the base and the shelf support structure to provide an axis of rotation, such that the shelf support structure and the shelf or shelves are selectively rotatable with respect to the axis. The swivel mechanism may include a race that defines a socket on a circumference of the race. A pin is selectively engageable with the socket to prevent rotation of the race and the support structure. The shelf may include a thermoformed plastic tray, or three shelves arranged at three different levels of the shelf support structure. Some of the shelves may fold against and secure to the shelf support structure.

column12: MicroRNA Transcriptional Signature (miR-TS) Evaluation of Stem Cells
column13: Aspects of the present disclosure include methods of evaluating stem cells. Aspects of the methods include obtaining a microRNA transcriptional signature (miR-TS), i.e., a microRNA transcriptional phenotype, for a stem cell and using the obtained miR-TS to evaluate the stem cell. Also provided are kits and compositions for practicing the subject methods. The methods and compositions find use in a variety of different applications, including diagnostic applications, therapeutic applications, research applications, and the like.

column13: The present methods and compositions are of use for treatment of conditions involving fibrosis, such as Peyronie's disease plaque, penile corporal fibrosis, penile veno-occlusive dysfunction, Dupuytren's disease nodules, vaginal fibrosis, clitoral fibrosis, female sexual arousal disorder, abnormal wound healing, keloid formation, general fibrosis of the kidney, bladder, prostate, skin, liver, lung, heart, intestines or any other localized or generalized fibrotic condition, vascular fibrosis, arterial intima hyperplasia, atherosclerosis, arteriosclerosis, restenosis, cardiac hypertrophy, hypertension or any condition characterized by excessive fibroblast or smooth muscle cell proliferation or deposition of collagen and extracellular matrix in the blood vessels and/or heart. column12: NMDA receptor blockers in the therapy of urogenital disease
column13: Methods are presented for the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia. The methods provide for administration to a person at least one compound identified generically as antagonists of N-methyl-D-aspartate receptors. These compounds are selected from the group consisting of memantidine, amantidine, dextromethorphan and ketamine.

column12: Methods of Use of Inhibitors of Phosphodiesterases and Modulators of Nitric Oxide, Reactive Oxygen Species, and Metalloproteinases in the Treatment of Peyronie's Disease, Arteriosclerosis and Other Fibrotic Diseases
column13: The present methods and compositions are of use for treatment of conditions involving fibrosis, such as Peyronie's disease plaque, penile corporal fibrosis, penile veno-occlusive dysfunction, Dupuytren's disease nodules, vaginal fibrosis, clitoral fibrosis, female sexual arousal disorder, abnormal wound healing, keloid formation, general fibrosis of the kidney, bladder, prostate, skin, liver, lung, heart, intestines or any other localized or generalized fibrotic condition, vascular fibrosis, arterial intima hyperplasia, atherosclerosis, arteriosclerosis, restenosis, cardiac hypertrophy, hypertension or any condition characterized by excessive fibroblast or smooth muscle cell proliferation or deposition of collagen and extracellular matrix in the blood vessels and/or heart. In certain embodiments, the compositions may comprise a PDE-4 inhibitor, a PDE-5 inhibitor, a compound that elevates cGMP and/or PKG, a stimulator of guanylyl cyclase and/or PKG, a combination of a compound that elevates cGMP, PKG or NO with an antioxidant that decreases ROS, or a compound that increases MMP activity.

column12: TWO-STROKE INNER COMBUSTION ENGINE.
column13: The present invention refers to a two-stroke inner combustion engine, where the pistons are actuated by a camshaft, and the mechanism of the exhaust valves allow the aperture thereof to be speed up or slow down, providing the following advantages: 1) A better use of the fuel. 2) Elimination of noise from the exhaust system upon equalling the pressure in the combustion chamber and the atmospheric pressure. 3) Elimination of detonation noise. 4) A higher power upon using the whole expansive wave of the combustion. 5) The same power upon modifying the compression ratio and maintaining the same air volume at different heights.

column12: AMELIORATION OF HUMAN ERECTILE DYSFUNCTION BY TREATMENT WITH iNOS, AND RELATED NOS AGENTS
column13: Treatment of erectile dysfunction comprising administering to a patient, inducible Nitric Oxide Synthase (iNOS) agents, including penile iNOS, inducers of penile iNOS, iNOS cDNA, or penile smooth muscle cells or corpora cavernosa with iNOS cDNA. Typical in vivo treatment involves delivery of these agents to the penile tissue of a patient by constant or intermittent implanted or external infusion pump, pellets, intrauretheral administration, injection or other related procedures. The genetically engineered cells or penile tissue from the patient hyperexpressing iNOS is implanted in microcapsules, pellets, or other methods, or directly by surgical inoculation into the corpora cavernosa. In certain cases, an oral or injectable systemic route of administration is applicable. Also disclosed are methods of treatment involving in vitro induction of iNOS in cultured smooth muscle cells and thereofter delivery of purified or recombinant iNOS enzyme, production of iNOS cDNA and genetic transformation with iNOS cDNA, followed by delivery thereof to the penis of a patient. The methods of this invention include hyperexpression and/or biological modulation of other endogenous and exogenous NOS isoforms in the penis, for the treatment of erectile dysfunction.

column12: AMELIORATION OF ERECTILE DYSFUNCTION
column13: Methods of treatment of erectile dysfunction are disclosed. In these methods, a medicament is introduced into the penile tissue of a patient. This medicament preferably is one which induces cavernosal smooth muscle relaxation, and/or produces an increase in the level of nitric oxide synthetase (NOS) in tissue. This treatment includes the transfer of cDNAs to the penis, wherein these cDNAs encode proteins that induce the relaxation of the corpora cavernosa smooth muscle. An isolated sequence encoding human penile inducible nitric oxide synthetase is also disclosed.

column12: LIGHTING DEVICE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING SAID LIGHTING DEVICE
column13: The lighting device comprises a light guide comprising two or more layers; and a light source that illuminates the light guide. The two or more layers define at least one surface between two adjacent layers. Geometric motives are formed in the at least one surface. The method for manufacturing the lighting device includes the step of providing one layer. Geometric motives are then formed in the one layer. column12: Method and system for providing location, tracking, assistance and bidirectional communication services for tourists.
column13: Method and system for providing location, tracking, assistance and bidirectional communication services for tourists.A method and system for personalised information and guidance, depending on the location of the user, used for example, as a personal guide for tourists, which includes in a Portable User Interface a location device such as the GPS/dGPS satellite positioning system to locate the user by means of a portable receiver. By means of a bidirectional communication system such as a mobile telephone, the user is kept in contact with a service providing centre by sending data such as the position of the user, personal preferences of the user or access to emergency services; the said services can be managed by a human operator or even automatically. The components permit the user to exercise control over the information he receives, and also to access services outside the system, such as, for example, the telephone service. The system can provide services to individual users or groups or gatherings.

column12: METODO Y SISTEMA PARA PRESTAR SERVICIOS DE LOCALIZACION, SEGUIMIENTO, ASISTENCIA Y COMUNICACION BIDIRECCIONAL A TURISTAS.
column13: Un método y sistema para información y guía personalizado en función del punto de ubicación del usuario, utilizado por ejemplo para guía turística de personas, integra en una Interface portátil de usuario un dispositivo de ubicación tal como un sistema de posicionamiento por satélite GPS/dGPS para localizar al usuario, a través de un receptor portátil. Mediante un sistema de comunicación bidireccional como un teléfono móvil, se mantiene en contacto al usuario con un centro proveedor de servicios, transmitiendo datos como posición del usuario, preferencias personalizadas por el usuario o acceso a servicios de emergencia; dichos servicios pueden ser gestionados por un operario humano o bien servicios de tipo automatizado. Los componentes permiten al usuario ejercer control sobre la información que recibe, también acceder a servicios ajenos al sistema, como por ejemplo el servicio telefónico. El sistema puede prestar servicios a usuarios individuales o bien a grupos o colectivos.

column12: CONNECTION DEVICE FOR CORRUGATED PIPING.
column13: The present invention refers to a connection device which coupling is hermetic for a short and long term, the device being useful for performing the attachment of a drainage piping to a current piping of higher diameter, the coupling being performed in a mechanical and manual form within a hole previously performed in the current piping, even when the same is being operated. The invention consists of an arrangement of four thermoplastic pieces, three of said pieces are semi-rigid, two are tubular elements threaded therebetween, and the fourth piece being a curved washer with an outer diameter higher than the hole diameter and flexible in the curved direction, which allows the same to be more curved so as to be introduced into the hole, but which are turned into more rigid upon being assembled, thereby generating a suitable contact with the inner surface of the current piping, once the pieces are located therein they may not be removed; the pieces are coaxially assembled and perfectly aligned due to the complementary form of the adjacent surfaces by means of a thread, which provides the required force to fix the arrangement to the piping.

column12: IMPROVEMENTS IN PURIFIER WITH CONTROLLED OZONE SUPPLY AND PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION THEREOF.
column13: The present invention refers to improvements in a purifier with controlled ozone supply and process for the production thereof. The purifier comprises one or a plurality of water filtering and ozonization units, the improvements being characterized in that they comprise a system including: a first 12 volts transformer to feed low voltage to an electronic board; a second transformer having an outlet for a variety of voltages for an automotive coil which supplies high voltage to the ozonization unit; a rectifying hub for voltage which is fed to a coil; a maximum flow regulator; a first filter mounting with minimum, to retain solids in suspension, comprising silica sand, granulated activated carbon to retain chemical products such as chlorine and other; the ozonization unit comprising the automotive coil and a power card to allow coils to oscillate, which is mounted over a heat sink; the second transformer energizes the coil according to a required function; the coil is coupled with an electronic oscillator to adjust the electric frequency, thereby predefining ozone concentrations; the ozonization unit comprises an air filter assembly, an ozone generator and an ozonized air injector for injecting air into a mixing chamber to homogenize water and ozone, which preferably comprises a Venturi, a diaphragm and a static mixture element; a water outlet and security valve; and an electronic system comprising an electric terminal multi-connector, wherein the connections are disposed and arranged; from said multi-connector transformer lines are derived, which increase the ozone generator voltage, as well as operation pointer lines, failure sensors and protection fuses.

column12: EMULADOR UNIVERSAL DE DISPOSITIVOS DE INTERFACES HUMANAS PARA USUARIOS DISCAPACITADOS.
column13: Emulador universal de dispositivos de interfaces humanas para usuarios discapacitados. La presente invención consiste en un dispositivo electrónico destinado a ser conectado al bus USB (Universal Serial Bus) de un ordenador personal con objeto de que al mismo se puedan conectar tras una adecuada configuración cualquier tipo de interfaces humanas como pueden ser un teclado, ratón, joystick controlador de juegos, pantalla táctil, etc. El emulador universal está especialmente destinado a facilitar el acceso de personas discapacitadas a equipos informáticos, cualquiera que sea el tipo de discapacidad de los mismos, y consiste en un dispositivo que se conecta al bus USB (Universal Serial Bus) de un ordenador personal convencional, y está capacitado para gestionar cualquier interfaz de usuario que se desee para lo cual el emulador es configurable.

column12: VISUALIZATION OF 4D DYNAMIC PULSATILE FLOW
column13: Systems and methods for monitoring pulsatile flows are disclosed. One method includes obtaining a plurality of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scans of a biological structure, acquired consecutively in time, each of the MRI scans acquired using a modified True FISP sequence. The method also includes assembling the plurality of scans into a video file of the biological structure and identifying pulsatile features within the video file.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO DE REPARACION DE SEPARADORES PLASTICOS Y SEPARADOR PLASTICO OBTENIDO POR DICHO PROCEDIMIENTO
column13: Procedimiento de reparacion de separadores (1) plasticos, del tipo que comprenden unos alveolos (100) internos longitudinales, que comprende las siguientes etapas: identificacion y extraccion de las zonas danadas a reparar (2), quedando determinados unos huecos (4), preparacion de unos injertos (5) de forma correspondiente con dichos huecos (4), y union mediante terrnosoldaduras (6) de los injertos (5) en los huecos (4); donde la extraccion de las zonas danadas a reparar se realiza mediante cortes (3) de trayectoria curva, y donde en la etapa de preparacion de los injertos (5) se mecanizan injertos con un borde exterior (50) alineado con los bordes (10) de! separador (1), y un borde interior (51) paralelo a la trayectoria curva del corte (3), quedando definido entre corte (3) practicado en el separador (1) y el borde interior (51) del injerto (5) un espacio para relleno (7) con material de aporte (8).

column12: Method for modifying myostatin expression
column13: A method comprising inhibiting myostatin expression or activity to increase muscle mass. Still further, methods for locally inhibiting myostatin expression or activity to reduce fibrosis are provided. The method comprises introducing a nucleotide sequence into a vector wherein the nucleotide sequence is expressed as a shRNA having a property to inhibit myostatin expression. The vector including the sequence may be delivered to a mammalian tissue. An electrical pulse may be applied across a point of delivery. A composition comprising a vector having a nucleotide sequence wherein the nucleotide sequence is expressed as a shRNA having a property to inhibit myostatin expression is further provided.

column12: NEW IMMUNOSTIMULATORY COMPOUNDS
column13: The present invention relates to novel immunostimulatory molecules which are derived from the intestinal protozoan Entamoeba histolytica .The compounds have been found to be useful for enhancing and/or inducing an immune response in a subject in need thereof. Specifically, the compounds have been found to be useful for the treatment of cancer diseases, such as breast cancer, and parasitic diseases, such as leishmaniasis. The invention also provides pharmaceutical compositions comprising the novel compounds.

column12: METHOD FOR REPAIRING PLASTIC SEPARATORS AND PLASTIC SEPARATOR OBTAINED USING THE METHOD
column13: Disclosed is a method for repairing plastic separators (1) comprising longitudinal internal cavities (100), which comprises the following steps: identifying and removing the damaged areas (2) to be repaired, there being spaces (4) defined; preparing inserts (5) have a shape matching the spaces (4); and joining the inserts (5) in the gaps (4) by means of heat welds (8), wherein the damaged areas to be repaired are removed by means of cuts (3) having a curved path, and wherein, in the step of preparing the inserts (5), inserts are machined with an outer edge (50) aligned with the edges (10) of the separator (1) and with an inner edge (51) parallel to the curved path of the cut (3), a space (7) for filling with filler material (8) being defined between the cut (3) made in the separator (1) and the inner edge (51) of the insert (5).

column12: Procedimiento de reparacion de separadores plasticos y separador plastico obtenido por dicho procedimiento
column13: Procedimiento de reparación de separadores (1) plásticos, del tipo que comprenden unos alveolos (100) internos longitudinales, que comprende las siguientes etapas; -identificación y extracción de las zonas dañadas a reparar (2), quedando determinados unos huecos (4), -preparación de unos injertos (5) de forma correspondiente con dichos huecos (4), y -unión mediante termosoldaduras (8) de los injertos (5) en los huecos (4); -donde la extracción de las zonas dañadas a reparar se realiza mediante cortes (3) de trayectoria curva, y -donde en la etapa de preparación de los injertos (5) se mecanizan injertos con un borde exterior (50) alineado con los bordes (10) del separador (1), y un borde interior (51) paralelo a la trayectoria curva del corte (3), quedando definido entre el corte (3) practicado en el separador (1) y el borde interior (51) del injerto (5) un espacio para relleno (7) con material de aporte (8).

column12: MODULE FOR A LED LAMP.
column13: The present invention is a device or module with an LED lamp of compact dimensions for use in different lighting industries such as the automotive industry, the signaling industry or architectural industry. The module includes elements for simple and fast assembly, efficient production from a single plate and with structures for structural support and heat diffusion. Said device or module can be directly mounted in the application or on a supporting means made of insulating material. Said device or module additionally has two different types of connection which can be used independently or together, depending on the application.

column12: GRIP SURFACES
column13: Provided among other things is a method of forming a composite glove with a grip texture, comprising: (a) providing a coagulant-coated support layer that is a fabric layer or a polymeric layer; (b) dip applying to the support layer a foamed polymer dispersion comprising about 0.5% to about 2.0% by weight hygroscopic agent; (c) allowing a portion of the applied foamed polymer dispersion to coagulate based the coagulant diffusing from the support layer to form a partially coagulated foam layer; (d) washing the partially coagulated foam layer to remove uncoagulated polymer to form a coagulated foam layer; and (e) vulcanizing the coagulated foam layer to form a vulcanized open foam layer laminated to the support.

column12: Device for generating disturbances in an electrical grid
column13: The invention relates to a device for generating network disturbances at a generator. The device comprises an inductive voltage divider (34) including a control unit (2), a bench of 6 inductors (28 to 33) connected to one another via a matrix of 18 isolators (5 to 22) and 5 coupled switches (23 to 27). The following can be coupled to the divider (34): a set of transformers (40, 43); a bank of capacitors and resistors (75); and an overvoltage module (OVRT, 79). The device can be used to perform tests for generator (3) power values of between 0 kW and 8,000 kW. The overvoltage test is performed by passing short-circuit current through coils (77) coupled to coils (78), generating 403 different configurations and producing 2,821 different overvoltages using combinations of the inductors (28 to 33), isolators (5 to 16) and (17 to 22) and switches (24 to 27).

column12: SOLID COMPOSITION FOR AGRICULTURAL AND VETERINARY USE
column13: A solid composition for agricultural or veterinary use, comprising a mixture of a bacterial concentrate of strain C-924 and a culture medium or a commercially available organic amendment, an antifoam substance and sucrose, and having less than 12% of residual moisture. The components of the formulation ensure adequate wettability of the finished solid product and extended storage stability at temperatures of 2 to 8°C. The invention discloses the use of the solid composition to control of plant and animal pathogens, and to stimulate seed germination and plant growth.

column12: MÉTODO DE PURIFICACIÓN DE GASES DE DESECHO CON RECUPERACIÓN DE AMONIACO
column13: La invención está relacionada con el campo de la protección del medio ambiente y en particular con la purificación de afluentes gaseosos . Su objetivo es lograr la purificación de corrientes gaseosas contaminadas con amoníaco mediante el empleo de tamices moleculares baratos de alta eficiencia de remoción que permiten recuperar amoníaco. Se explica un método de purificación de gases de desechos industriales que contienen concentraciones de amoníaco tan altas como 50 000 ppm empleando tamices moleculares obtenidos a partir de zeolitas naturales cálcicas por procedimientos de intercambio iónico alcanzando niveles de remoción mayores del 99% del amoníaco El método ofrece variantes de regeneración del absorbente que permiten recuperar el amoníaco y opcionalmente variantes no recuperativas con o sin regeneración. Es aplicable en sistemas de purificación industrial en procesos de fabricación de fertilizantes y otros procesos e instalaciones industriales donde el amoníaco aparece como contaminante , así como para adsorbedores a escala pequena en filtros de protección individual.empleando tamices moleculares obtenidos a partir de zeolitas naturales cálcicas por procedimientos de intercambio iónico alcanzando niveles de remoción mayores del 99% del amoníaco

column12: Filtered Smoking Articles
column13: A smoking article is provided including (a) a tobacco rod comprising a smokable filler material contained within a circumscribing outer wrapping material, wherein the smokable filler material comprises at least about 45% by weight flue-cured tobacco based on the total dry weight of the smokable filler material; (b) one or more inner wrapping strips positioned between the tobacco rod and the outer wrapping material and extending longitudinally along the tobacco rod and including a burley tobacco; and (c) a filter element connected to the tobacco rod, the filter element having an end proximal to the tobacco rod and an end distal from the tobacco rod, wherein the filter element includes at least one fibrous tow section of filter material, a general adsorbent, and an ion exchange resin.

column12: Environmentally adaptable transport device
column13: Disclosed is a device for the transport of temperature sensitive products including an insulated container, an insulated lid, a fastener to secure the lid to the container, an active heat exchanger, a thermal circuit to circulate heat exchange, a temperature sensor read by a temperature regulating circuit that maintains a temperature range, a power source, and a support frame that arranges the elements of the device with the overall center of mass at a location adapted for transport and storage of the device. Disclosed is also a method of transport for temperature sensitive products including securing the temperature sensitive product within an insulated container with a lid, removing heat from the container to maintain a temperature range, strapping the device onto the user's back and adjusting to the shape of the user, freeing both hands during transport of the device, and minimizing hindrances to user mobility caused by the device.

column12: SEGMENTED SMOKING ARTICLE WITH INSULATION MAT

column12: ENVIRONMENTALLY ADAPTABLE TRANSPORT DEVICE
column13: Disclosed is a device for the transport of temperature sensitive products including an insulated container, an insulated lid, a fastener to secure the lid to the container, an active heat exchanger, a thermal circuit to circulate heat exchange, a temperature sensor read by a temperature regulating circuit that maintains a temperature range, a power source, and a support frame that arranges the elements of the device with the overall center of mass at a location adapted for transport and storage of the device. Disclosed is also a method of transport for temperature sensitive products including securing the temperature sensitive product within an insulated container with a lid, removing heat from the container to maintain a temperature range, strapping the device onto the user's back and adjusting to the shape of the user, freeing both hands during transport of the device, and minimizing hindrances to user mobility caused by the device.

column12: PROCESO DE PURIFICACIÓN DE POLIPÉPTIDOS MULTIEPITÓPICOS (MEPS)
column13: Desarrollo de un proceso para la obtención de Polipéptidos Multiepitópicos para la eliminación de los contaminantes derivados de la cepa hospedera, Escherichia coli K12, y otras fuentes. Esencialmente consiste en un lavado diferencial del precipitado celular insoluble con un detergente (Tritón X-100) y un agente desnaturalizante (Urea). La extracción se efectúa a molaridades relativamente elevadas de este mismo agente. El proceso cromatográfico consta de tres pasos. El fraccionamiento, donde se utiliza una matriz utilizando una matriz de filtración en gel. Los polipéptidos Multiepitópicos purificados y renaturalizados apropiadamente pueden ser utilizados en el diágnostico y como preparado vacunal al formularse con el adyuvante oleoso Montanide ISA 720. Los polipéptidos Multiepitópicos purificados y los anticuerpos generados contra ellos pueden tener utilidad en el diagnóstico, la terapéutica o la prevención del SIDA.

column12: SEGMENTED SMOKING ARTICLE WITH SUBSTRATE CAVITY
column13: An aerosol-generation system for a smoking article comprises a heat generation segment including an insulation layer of flame-retardant material and an aerosol-generating segment including a tobacco substrate and incorporating aerosol-forming material, the tobacco substrate being disposed within a substrate cavity, in which the tobacco substrate is dimensioned to fit within the substrate cavity. The system also comprises a wrapping material circumscribing at least a portion of the heat generation segment and the aerosol-generating segment. The wrapping material comprises a foil strip circumferentially encompassing and extending lengthwise along at least a lengthwise portion of the substrate cavity and overlapping at least a lengthwise portion of the heat generation segment. The wrapping material also comprises a paper material, and the foil strip is laminated to a surface of the paper material, registered for alignment with the substrate cavity at a predetermined location.

column12: UNIVERSAL RECONFIGURABLE SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR THE REMOTE READING OF COUNTERS OR EQUIPMENT COMPRISING VISUAL INDICATORS
column13: The invention relates to a system (1) for the remote reading of counters (5) or equipment comprising visual data indicators (6), which is characterised in that it is based on the use of reconfigurable logic devices (9) and in that it can be remotely reconfigured, thereby converting said system (1) into a universal system which is suitable for any type of counter (5) and which can be adapted to variations in the installation or operation conditions of the counter (5) or the system (1) itself. The invention also relates to reconfiguration methods, image capture methods, etc., which are characterised in that they comprise the parallel implementation of tasks with the use of queues, thereby reducing the capacity or quantity of data storage memories needed.

column12: UNIVERSAL RECONFIGURABLE SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR THE REMOTE READING OF COUNTERS OR EQUIPMENT COMPRISING VISUAL INDICATORS
column13: System (1) for remotely reading a meter (5) or equipment fitted with data visual indicators (6), which is  characterized in that  it is based on the use of reprogrammable logic devices (9) and the fact that it can be remotely reprogrammed. These two features make the system (1) universal, i.e., suitable for all types of meters (5), and adjustable to all types of variations in the installation or operation conditions of the meter (5) or the system (1) itself. Methods for reconfiguration, image capture, etc. are defined, having in common that some actions are carried out in parallel, with the use of queues, therefore requiring a small number of (or low-capacity) data storage memory components.

column12: INSOLE FOR STATIC MEASUREMENT OF PLANTAR PRESSURE.
column13: The present disclosure is related to an insole for static measurement of plantar pressure, specifically, to the design of a mat to measure the plantar pressure of both feet in a static manner. Consists of pressure sensitive sensors that provide different signals that are acquired by an embedded system and transferred by means of a serial cable. Enabling a podiatrist, physiotherapist, physical therapy graduates, rehabilitation physicians, neurologists, orthopedic and trauma physicians and sports medicine, obtain the necessary data in diagnostic processes, evaluation treatment of foot conditions. The sensors are distributed in a insole for the right foot and another for the left foot, where the patient places the feet, allowing determining with certainty the type of foot that the patient has. The advantage of the present invention is that various foot sizes can be monitored.
